# Presentation on Latin squares in Lean (George)

George presented his joint work on formalizing Latin squares in Lean and submitting the final result into Lean's Mathlib.

Note, an important resource for this and generally learning about Lean/Mathlib is the Lean Zulip chat.

The code and the pull request are available here: https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/36698
The associated Zulip chat: https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.2336698.20feat.28Combinatorics.2FEnumerative.29.3A.20Latin.20squares

# Discussion of projects

To jump start some of our projects, we discussed in two weeks' time having a longer "drop-in" meeting where people can co-work together on getting some Lean projects going.
Having more time will allow us to get into technical details and people can come and go as they need during the session.

*Tentative date*: Monday, April 6th.

In preparation, if you have a project you want to work on, we ask that you have the mathematical portion of the project well-prepared, that is, make sure you have a detailed mathematical sketch of how the result(s) you want to prove are actually proven.
